<item>
            <title>[SEC-451] Empty context path in LogoutFilter and AbstractProcessingFilter</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-451</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When context path is empty, LogoutFilter erroneously believes &quot;/anything/before/j_acegi_logout&quot; is a logout URL.  The requiresLogout() method should use &lt;b&gt;uri.equals(request.getContextPath() + filterProcessesUrl)&lt;/b&gt; instead of &lt;b&gt;uri.endsWith(request.getContextPath() + filterProcessesUrl)&lt;/b&gt;, or more simple, &lt;b&gt;uri.endsWith(filterProcessesUrl)&lt;/b&gt; to detect any URL ending with &lt;b&gt;j_acegi_logout&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="16341">SEC-451</key>
            <summary>Empty context path in LogoutFilter and AbstractProcessingFilter</summary>
